02:48.269 --> 02:49.869
Hey, you think
it'd be okay

02:49.871 --> 02:51.504
if I brought Claire
to the wine tasting?

02:51.506 --> 02:53.305
Sure. I'd like to meet her.
Oh, that's great.

02:53.307 --> 02:54.974
I've been wanting her
to meet you guys, too,

02:54.976 --> 02:56.609
so this seems like
the perfect opportunity.

02:56.611 --> 02:58.110
Oh, but I won't be there.

02:58.112 --> 02:59.445
Funny how that worked out.

03:00.848 --> 03:03.449
Does this mean Emily's not
in the picture anymore?

03:03.451 --> 03:04.517
No, I'm still dating her.

03:04.519 --> 03:05.685
Okay, help me out.

03:05.687 --> 03:07.019
How are you doing this?

03:07.021 --> 03:08.854
Do they know about each other?

03:08.856 --> 03:10.589
They know that
we're not exclusive,

03:10.591 --> 03:12.725
and we just don't ask
too many questions.

03:12.727 --> 03:15.361
You know, it's like how I play
Warlords of Ka'a with you

03:15.363 --> 03:19.131
and Elder Sign with
Frank and Alicia.

03:20.234 --> 03:21.701
Who's Frank and Alicia?

03:21.703 --> 03:24.136
Y... You and I spend
a lot of time together.

03:24.138 --> 03:26.739
Can there be a little
mystery between us?

03:26.741 --> 03:28.507
Okay.

03:28.509 --> 03:30.276
Everything's hooked up.
We're ready.

03:30.278 --> 03:33.212
I am going to record
this for posterity.

03:33.214 --> 03:34.914
All right, here goes nothing.

03:34.916 --> 03:36.282
Here goes nothing?

03:36.284 --> 03:37.917
This is the initial test
of our prototype.

03:37.919 --> 03:39.518
Can we give it
a little more gravitas?

03:39.520 --> 03:40.686
Fine.

03:40.688 --> 03:43.489
Preliminary trial
of the infinite persistence

03:43.491 --> 03:46.559
gyroscopic navigational system:
phase one commencing.

03:46.561 --> 03:47.927
Eh... maybe it's your voice.

03:47.929 --> 03:50.763
I'm gonna see if I can get James
Earl Jones to do it in post.

03:55.403 --> 03:56.969
Ooh.

03:58.773 --> 04:00.473
Wow.

04:00.475 --> 04:03.109
It's... it's-it's beautiful.

04:05.413 --> 04:07.346
Actually,
it's making me dizzy.

04:07.348 --> 04:10.049
Good, it's not just me.

04:15.223 --> 04:16.387
Hello.

04:16.390 --> 04:17.423
Hey, Claire.

04:17.425 --> 04:18.390
Hey, what's up?

04:18.392 --> 04:19.125
Hi, yeah.

04:19.127 --> 04:20.625
Um, I was wondering,

04:20.628 --> 04:22.795
if you're free Saturday night,

04:22.797 --> 04:25.097
all my friends are
going to a wine tasting.

04:25.099 --> 04:27.500
Sure, I guess.

04:27.502 --> 04:30.169
If you don't think meeting
your friends is too big a step.

04:30.171 --> 04:32.705
Why would it be too big a step?

04:32.707 --> 04:35.875
I don't know. I just don't
want things to get weird.

04:36.744 --> 04:38.944
Nothing to worry about.

04:38.946 --> 04:40.379
People meet people all the time,

04:40.381 --> 04:41.847
and it isn't weird.

04:41.849 --> 04:44.383
I met Bon Jovi once, which
you'd think might be weird.

04:44.385 --> 04:47.353
Turns out, total sweetheart.

04:47.355 --> 04:51.524
Okay, but you and I have been
keeping things casual.

04:51.526 --> 04:53.559
Uh, will you introduce me
as your friend

04:53.561 --> 04:54.727
or as your girlfriend?

04:54.729 --> 04:56.295
What if I like them

04:56.297 --> 04:57.429
and they don't like me?

04:57.431 --> 04:59.532
What if they like me
and I don't like them?

04:59.534 --> 05:02.368
Boy, it wasn't this hard
with Bon Jovi.

05:02.370 --> 05:04.403
I said, “You rock,”
he said, “Thanks, man,”

05:04.405 --> 05:07.273
and that was that.

05:14.615 --> 05:16.015
Hey, you ready to go?

05:16.017 --> 05:17.950
Hang on.
What are you doing?

05:17.952 --> 05:21.787
Oh, I found a scratch-and-sniff
book about wine tasting.

05:22.824 --> 05:24.957
It teaches the different
flavor notes to look for.

05:24.959 --> 05:26.559
You actually smell the wine?

05:26.561 --> 05:29.128
I mostly just smell
my nasal spray.

05:29.130 --> 05:31.197
Are your sinuses acting up?

05:31.199 --> 05:32.898
Since my preschool got a bunny.

05:32.900 --> 05:35.935
Hey, are you still hanging out
with Bernadette tonight?

05:35.937 --> 05:37.269
Yes.

05:37.271 --> 05:39.305
And we're going to prove
that we don't need alcohol

05:39.307 --> 05:40.339
to enjoy ourselves.

05:40.341 --> 05:41.674
Oh, good for you.

05:41.676 --> 05:43.609
Or caffeine, tobacco, sushi,

05:43.611 --> 05:46.278
soft cheese, processed meats
and Jacuzzis,

05:46.280 --> 05:48.881
which can all be harmful
to an unborn baby.

05:48.883 --> 05:52.351
No HoneyBaked Ham
in a hot tub-- got it.

05:52.353 --> 05:53.686
Oh, no bubble baths either.

05:53.688 --> 05:55.821
They can increase the risk
of a urinary tract infection.

05:55.823 --> 05:57.089
Okay, have fun.

05:57.091 --> 05:59.992
Oh, and no swordfish, king
mackerel, shark or tilefish,

05:59.994 --> 06:01.527
which are all high in mercury.

06:01.529 --> 06:02.661
We're leaving now!

06:02.663 --> 06:03.863
Oh, and no contact with
guinea pigs

06:03.865 --> 06:05.164
or hamsters or their droppings,

06:05.166 --> 06:08.467
uh, no-no cat litter boxes,
no paint fumes...

06:08.469 --> 06:10.970
Okay, we're leaving,
love you, bye!

06:12.240 --> 06:14.840
Boy, do I love restrictions.

06:16.043 --> 06:18.477
Hey.

06:18.479 --> 06:19.511
Where is everybody?

06:19.513 --> 06:21.146
Oh, we're the first ones here.

06:21.148 --> 06:22.915
Oh.

06:22.917 --> 06:25.017
Cool.

06:25.019 --> 06:26.785
Yeah.

06:26.787 --> 06:28.220
Cool.

06:34.562 --> 06:36.028
You know, I don't
remember the last time

06:36.030 --> 06:37.796
it was just you and me
hanging out.

06:37.798 --> 06:40.766
Oh, I do.
It was three years ago.

06:40.768 --> 06:44.203
Oh, yeah, and we said
we should do it more often.

06:44.205 --> 06:46.939
And-and here we are.

06:54.649 --> 06:56.682
So, Sheldon and Bernadette
are hanging out.

06:56.684 --> 07:00.052
I know. What are they
gonna talk about?

07:01.522 --> 07:03.622
I don't know.

07:03.624 --> 07:06.992
I really don't know.

07:06.994 --> 07:07.927
Hey.

07:07.929 --> 07:09.495
Oh, good!
Oh, thank God!

07:09.497 --> 07:11.764
You guys been here long?

07:11.766 --> 07:12.798
No, two minutes.

07:12.800 --> 07:15.601
But yes.

07:15.603 --> 07:16.635
Where's Claire?

07:16.637 --> 07:18.070
Oh, she's meeting us here.

07:18.072 --> 07:20.339
Hey, guys, do me a favor
and don't ask too many questions

07:20.341 --> 07:21.307
about the relationship.

07:21.309 --> 07:22.875
We're just keeping it casual.

07:22.877 --> 07:25.611
Oh, so I shouldn't ask her
how she feels about being

07:25.613 --> 07:27.780
a member of your harem?

07:27.782 --> 07:30.849
Yeah, I know you're teasing,
but watch out for karma.

07:30.851 --> 07:33.585
Hey, Penny, isn't that
your old boyfriend Zack?

07:33.587 --> 07:35.654
Oh, yeah.

07:35.656 --> 07:37.122
Are you gonna
say hi to him?

07:37.124 --> 07:38.257
Uh, I don't know.

07:38.259 --> 07:39.258
Hey, while you decide,

07:39.260 --> 07:40.526
who was better in bed:

07:40.528 --> 07:43.963
big hot Zack
or wheezy little Leonard?

07:46.000 --> 07:49.101
Neener neener.

07:50.271 --> 07:51.870
I brought sparkling cider.

07:51.872 --> 07:55.074
Oh... the bubbles
tickle my nose.

07:55.076 --> 07:57.509
I'll just open this now
so it can get

07:57.511 --> 08:00.112
nice and flat
before we drink it.

08:00.114 --> 08:02.114
So what do you want
to do tonight?

08:02.116 --> 08:04.350
Oh, I have quite
the evening planned.

08:04.352 --> 08:07.653
Our fetus-friendly
festival of fun begins

08:07.655 --> 08:08.954
with an in-depth look

08:08.956 --> 08:10.889
at the world of model trains,

08:10.891 --> 08:13.192
and then we'll kick things
up a notch and explore

08:13.194 --> 08:16.328
all the different ways
that you can make toast.

08:16.330 --> 08:18.297
There's more than one?

08:19.166 --> 08:21.133
You've heard of French toast?
Yeah.

08:21.135 --> 08:22.401
Cinnamon toast?
Yeah.

08:22.403 --> 08:23.635
Melba toast?
Yeah.

08:23.637 --> 08:25.871
You get where I'm going here?

08:25.873 --> 08:28.374
Yeah.

08:30.478 --> 08:33.312
I'm getting
an earthy note.

08:33.313 --> 08:35.246
Ah, there's
definitely some oak.

08:35.249 --> 08:37.515
Also, uh, cherries?

08:37.518 --> 08:39.451
I smell nothing.

08:40.755 --> 08:43.022
Really? Nothing?

08:43.024 --> 08:46.625
Just a... whole lot of Afrin.

08:46.627 --> 08:48.360
Penny?

08:48.362 --> 08:49.595
Oh. Zack, hi!

08:49.597 --> 08:50.863
You guys remember Zack.

08:50.865 --> 08:51.997
Yeah, hey, buddy.
- Hello. - Hey.

08:51.999 --> 08:53.866
Hey, did you two
get married?

08:53.868 --> 08:55.167
We did.
Yeah, mm-hmm.

08:55.169 --> 08:57.403
To each other?

08:58.672 --> 09:00.105
Yes.

09:00.107 --> 09:02.307
Cool. 'Cause other than
when you broke up with him

09:02.309 --> 09:04.009
and dated me, then
broke up with me,

09:04.011 --> 09:06.945
and then dated me one more
time before going back to him,

09:06.947 --> 09:08.914
I was always rooting
for you two.

09:08.916 --> 09:10.549
Thanks.

09:10.551 --> 09:12.051
So how's the
science world?

09:12.053 --> 09:13.485
What are you
guys up to?

09:13.487 --> 09:15.888
W-We've actually been
working on a prototype

09:15.890 --> 09:17.423
for a navigation
system we invented.

09:17.425 --> 09:19.224
But we won't bore you
with the details.

09:19.226 --> 09:21.393
Are you kidding?
I love science.

09:21.395 --> 09:24.997
Einstein, Stephen Hawking,
Mike deGrasse Tyson.

09:25.866 --> 09:28.000
Mike deGrasse Tyson?

09:28.002 --> 09:30.702
Yeah, you know,
the boxer who grew a mustache

09:30.704 --> 09:33.305
and became a scientist.

09:33.307 --> 09:34.573
So what's your
invention?

09:34.575 --> 09:37.776
Well, we're using
quantum vortices

09:37.778 --> 09:39.978
to replace gyroscopes
in guidance systems.

09:39.980 --> 09:41.680
What's neat is
that they can maintain

09:41.682 --> 09:43.348
angular momentum indefinitely.

09:43.350 --> 09:45.551
Angular momentum.

09:45.553 --> 09:48.020
I was wondering about that.

09:48.022 --> 09:51.790
You could put it in a
satellite or a rocket,

09:51.792 --> 09:53.559
and it'll run forever.

09:53.561 --> 09:54.827
Cool.

09:54.829 --> 09:57.196
Could it be used for
missiles and war stuff?

09:57.198 --> 10:00.432
Yeah, but we didn't
create it for weapons.

10:00.434 --> 10:02.434
And I doubt the military
would be interested

10:02.436 --> 10:03.802
in our little
guidance system.

10:03.804 --> 10:05.404
Is it better than
the one they use now?

10:05.406 --> 10:08.207
A lot!
Way better.

10:08.209 --> 10:09.942
Huh.

10:09.944 --> 10:12.478
You sure you guys are smart?

