10:21.118 --> 10:24.586
“H-O” gauge trains
are 1/87 scale.

10:24.588 --> 10:27.789
“N” gauge are
1/160 scale.

10:27.791 --> 10:30.459
And that brings us
to “Z” gauge, at a

10:30.461 --> 10:35.264
“you could easily swallow it,
don't ask how I know,” 1/220.

10:35.266 --> 10:37.432
I'm sorry, I have to ask.

10:37.434 --> 10:40.569
When I was five, I ingested
a “Z” gauge locomotive.

10:40.571 --> 10:43.005
I spent the next three days
saying, “I think I can pass it,

10:43.007 --> 10:46.742
I think I can pass it,
I think I can pass it.”

10:48.212 --> 10:50.979
What is it about trains
that you like so much?

10:50.981 --> 10:53.148
What an interesting
question.

10:53.150 --> 10:56.118
When I was a child,
life was confusing

10:56.120 --> 10:59.121
and chaotic for me, and
trains represented order.

10:59.123 --> 11:03.158
I could line them up,
categorize them, control them.

11:03.160 --> 11:04.660
I guess you
could say that

11:04.662 --> 11:08.096
they gave me a sense of calm
in a world that didn't.

11:08.098 --> 11:10.165
That's lovely, Sheldon.

11:10.167 --> 11:12.868
Well... other than when they're
chugging through your bowels,

11:12.870 --> 11:14.703
these things are magic.

11:17.708 --> 11:19.675
I have to admit,
I've been worried about

11:19.677 --> 11:22.678
the military applications since
we started talking about this.

11:22.680 --> 11:24.046
Me, too.

11:24.048 --> 11:25.380
Why didn't you
say something?

11:25.382 --> 11:27.816
Same reason I don't
talk about ass cancer.

11:27.818 --> 11:30.786
It's not a
pleasant topic.

11:30.788 --> 11:32.354
You can't let this stop you.

11:32.356 --> 11:34.389
Almost any scientific
advancement can be used

11:34.391 --> 11:36.091
for destructive purposes.

11:36.093 --> 11:38.126
It's true. Even Einstein's
theory of relativity

11:38.128 --> 11:40.796
was later applied to the
development of nuclear weapons.

11:40.798 --> 11:42.631
E equals MC squared.

11:42.633 --> 11:43.999
Yeah.

11:44.001 --> 11:45.334
“E” is for energy,
“M” for mass,

11:45.336 --> 11:46.768
and “C” for the speed of light.

11:48.939 --> 11:50.505
How do you know that?

11:50.507 --> 11:54.109
Oh, Leonard mumbles it when
he wants sex to last longer.

11:57.214 --> 11:58.180
Hey, Raj.

11:58.182 --> 12:00.248
Hey, Claire.
Good, you're here.

12:00.250 --> 12:02.117
Guys, this is
my friend Claire.

12:02.119 --> 12:04.319
We're casually dating,
and there's no need

12:04.321 --> 12:06.755
for any further questions
about it.

12:07.524 --> 12:09.825
Would you like
a glass of wine?

12:09.827 --> 12:11.593
I said no questions!

12:13.697 --> 12:15.931
And last
but not least,

12:15.933 --> 12:19.935
this is one that I like to call
Star Wars Toast because...

12:19.937 --> 12:24.272
it has a light side
and a dark side.

12:26.977 --> 12:29.277
All righty, it's time for
Dungeons & Dragons!

12:29.279 --> 12:31.647
Dungeons & Dragons.

12:31.649 --> 12:32.981
That sounds about right.

12:32.983 --> 12:35.517
You're gonna
enjoy this.

12:35.519 --> 12:38.253
I designed it
especially for you.

12:38.255 --> 12:39.888
Okay, but just for a little bit.

12:39.890 --> 12:41.590
Oh, I have a feeling
that once you start,

12:41.592 --> 12:44.393
you're not gonna want to
or be allowed to stop.

12:44.395 --> 12:47.229
All right.

12:47.231 --> 12:48.230
Ready?

12:48.232 --> 12:49.998
You bet.

12:50.000 --> 12:51.633
Your name is

12:51.635 --> 12:52.734
Bernatrix.

12:52.736 --> 12:54.036
You are a warrior queen.

12:54.038 --> 12:56.905
You're strong,
beautiful and tall.

12:56.907 --> 13:00.709
Oh. I like the idea
of being tall.

13:00.711 --> 13:03.145
I think you're gonna like
a lot of things I have in store.

13:03.147 --> 13:05.747
For example, in this world,
only the men get pregnant,

13:05.749 --> 13:10.485
so your husband is home trying
not to pee when he laughs.

13:10.487 --> 13:12.454
This is getting fun.
What's next?

13:12.456 --> 13:14.623
You're parched and weary
from battle.

13:14.625 --> 13:17.893
You stand in front of a tavern
that serves the coldest,

13:17.895 --> 13:20.195
most delicious ale
in all the realm.

13:20.197 --> 13:22.564
Oh, I haven't had
a drink in months.

13:22.566 --> 13:24.299
What do you do?

13:24.301 --> 13:27.302
I storm in, slam my sword down,

13:27.304 --> 13:29.838
and say, “Barkeep, bring me
the strongest ale you have

13:29.840 --> 13:32.174
and serve it in
the skull of a goblin!”

13:35.112 --> 13:37.679
He wants to see I.D.

13:40.384 --> 13:43.552
So, Claire, we've heard so many
wonderful things about you.

13:43.554 --> 13:46.054
Really? Like what?

13:48.092 --> 13:50.358
Uh, mostly Penny's
heard them.

13:52.196 --> 13:54.930
Boy, you get some
dirty looks over there

13:54.932 --> 13:56.965
when you ask for ice.

13:57.735 --> 14:00.335
Zack, this is
my friend Claire.

14:00.337 --> 14:02.838
You're hot. You seeing anybody?

14:02.840 --> 14:04.940
Uh, she's seeing me.

14:04.942 --> 14:06.174
Why'd you say she's your friend?

14:06.176 --> 14:07.409
We're just
keeping it casual.

14:07.411 --> 14:09.644
Why is he being casual with you?
You seem great.

14:09.646 --> 14:11.046
I don't know. Ask him.

14:11.048 --> 14:13.415
Why are you being casual
with her? She seems great.

14:21.358 --> 14:23.725
Maybe we should
take a step back.

14:23.727 --> 14:25.260
Take a step back?

14:25.262 --> 14:27.362
I'm not a young man anymore.

14:28.766 --> 14:32.267
No, I mean reevaluate what we're
doing with the guidance system.

14:32.269 --> 14:34.836
But I got a baby
on the way.

14:34.838 --> 14:36.404
I got to make some money.

14:36.406 --> 14:37.939
What good is
money gonna do

14:37.941 --> 14:39.641
if we inadvertently
bring about Armageddon?

14:39.643 --> 14:41.409
Okay, let me stop you
right there.

14:41.411 --> 14:42.644
We absolutely know

14:42.646 --> 14:45.747
our invention will not be used
to destroy the world.

14:45.749 --> 14:46.815
How?

14:46.817 --> 14:48.183
Because no one from the future

14:48.185 --> 14:50.318
has come back to kill us.

14:52.156 --> 14:53.522
Very funny.

14:53.524 --> 14:54.956
You got something better?

14:54.958 --> 14:56.291
Well, not really.

14:56.293 --> 14:57.893
Okay, then.

15:03.200 --> 15:05.066
Geez, how much wine
did you drink?

15:05.068 --> 15:08.804
Not a lot. I just couldn't
start until you walked away.

15:12.176 --> 15:14.876
The Hell Prawn lunges
out of the hot spring!

15:15.879 --> 15:18.180
You block it with your shield.

15:18.182 --> 15:19.181
Do you attack?

15:19.183 --> 15:20.315
Does it have eyes?

15:20.317 --> 15:22.851
Three giant red ones
and they never blink.

15:22.853 --> 15:24.486
It's unsettling.

15:24.488 --> 15:27.022
I stab it in the middle eye!

15:28.325 --> 15:29.324
Good choice!

15:29.326 --> 15:30.926
Critical hit!
Your sword goes

15:30.928 --> 15:33.094
through its eye
into its tiny brain.

15:33.096 --> 15:35.397
With its final dying gasp,
it says,

15:35.399 --> 15:36.932
“You have reduced me

15:36.934 --> 15:38.867
“to a pile of sushi.

15:38.869 --> 15:40.535
“Enjoy me

15:40.537 --> 15:43.471
“with this packet of soy sauce.

15:43.473 --> 15:46.141
It's low sodium.”

15:47.845 --> 15:49.911
Okay, I guess I should
eat the Hell Prawn.

15:49.913 --> 15:50.879
Using your sword,

15:50.881 --> 15:53.181
you prepare a beautiful
sushi dinner.

15:53.183 --> 15:56.351
You slip into the hot spring
and enjoy the warm water

15:56.353 --> 15:57.485
on your aching joints.

15:57.487 --> 15:58.753
As you happily
close your eyes,

15:58.755 --> 16:01.056
you recall the incredible
evening you've had

16:01.058 --> 16:02.490
and notice that your...

16:03.894 --> 16:08.263
...feet and ankles are
smaller than they've ever been.

16:08.265 --> 16:09.931
The end.

16:09.933 --> 16:13.702
Wow, this night turned out to be
so much more fun than I thought.

16:13.704 --> 16:15.036
Oh, the fun doesn't stop.

16:15.038 --> 16:17.505
You're still going home
with a goodie bag full of toast.

16:20.777 --> 16:22.477
Thank you for this.

16:22.479 --> 16:25.180
You know, ever since people
found out I'm having a baby,

16:25.182 --> 16:27.983
I feel like I became
Pregnant Bernadette.

16:27.985 --> 16:30.118
It was nice to take
a little break tonight.

16:30.120 --> 16:32.254
I can understand that.

16:32.256 --> 16:34.623
From the moment
people realized I was a genius,

16:34.625 --> 16:36.424
I've been Sheldon the Genius.

16:38.328 --> 16:40.161
Although I've never really
wanted a break from that,

16:40.163 --> 16:41.796
so I suppose I don't understand.

16:41.798 --> 16:43.531
Which is ironic

16:43.533 --> 16:45.533
'cause, you know, genius.

16:47.738 --> 16:49.537
Well, thanks again.

16:49.539 --> 16:50.639
You're welcome.

16:50.641 --> 16:52.073
And any time you need a break

16:52.075 --> 16:53.475
from being
Bernadette the Pregnant,

16:53.477 --> 16:55.677
Bernatrix the Warrior Queen
is here waiting.

16:55.679 --> 16:57.646
I might just take
you up on that.

16:57.648 --> 16:58.980
Well, mind you now,

16:58.982 --> 17:01.416
that offer's only good
until the third trimester.

17:01.418 --> 17:05.153
I can't risk getting
amniotic fluid on my spot.

17:07.257 --> 17:10.692
Hey, dude, you're
killing me with Claire.

17:10.694 --> 17:11.760
What are you talking about?

17:11.762 --> 17:14.329
I mean,
come on, look at you.

17:14.330 --> 17:17.365
You're classically handsome,
you've got a swimmer's body.

17:17.367 --> 17:20.568
Next to you,
I look like me.

17:20.569 --> 17:23.637
Oh, man,
I didn't mean to do that.

17:23.640 --> 17:26.675
But I do appreciate you
recognizing my swimmer's body.

17:26.676 --> 17:28.910
Which, incidentally,

17:28.912 --> 17:31.980
I got from playing
Marco Polo at the YMCA.

17:34.017 --> 17:36.751
Yeah, okay, just...
do me a favor

17:36.753 --> 17:39.554
and stop talking about
how great Claire is.

17:39.556 --> 17:42.724
Anything for you,
my little foreign friend.

17:43.961 --> 17:45.360
So, I got to ask,

17:45.362 --> 17:47.429
does Raj bring around
other girls?

17:48.298 --> 17:49.798
Uh, you know,

17:49.800 --> 17:52.000
I-I'm not really
around that much.

17:52.002 --> 17:54.035
Amy knows much more
than I do.

17:55.439 --> 17:57.172
I don't think you have
anything to worry about.

17:57.174 --> 17:59.841
Raj is a terrific guy,
loyal to a fault.

17:59.843 --> 18:03.011
Yeah. He still has
an AOL address.

18:04.381 --> 18:05.914
I see what you're saying.

18:05.916 --> 18:08.917
She's not so great.

18:12.756 --> 18:14.656
Don't listen to him.

18:14.658 --> 18:16.524
He says crazy things
all the time.

18:16.526 --> 18:17.525
Uh, watch. Marco.

18:17.527 --> 18:19.260
Polo!

18:21.164 --> 18:24.299
So, uh, what are
you guys talking about?

18:24.301 --> 18:26.267
Your friends were
just telling me about

18:26.269 --> 18:27.869
all the other girls
you're dating.

18:27.871 --> 18:30.305
Why would you do that?

18:30.307 --> 18:32.974
I specifically asked you
not to do that.

18:32.976 --> 18:34.242
We didn't.

18:34.244 --> 18:35.510
You just did.

18:38.048 --> 18:41.549
Wow. Maybe none of
you guys are smart.

18:51.759 --> 18:53.825
Morning.

18:53.827 --> 18:55.026
Morning.

18:55.028 --> 18:57.060
Ugh. Too much wine.

18:57.061 --> 18:58.327
Oh, I overdid it

18:58.329 --> 18:59.628
myself last night.

18:59.630 --> 19:01.263
Hair of the dog.

19:02.867 --> 19:06.001
Hey, did you ever think about
the military applications

19:06.003 --> 19:07.570
for the guidance system?

19:07.572 --> 19:09.338
Of course.

19:09.340 --> 19:10.673
Does it bother you?

19:11.509 --> 19:13.309
No, it did at first,

19:13.311 --> 19:16.879
but then I talked it through
with Frank and Alicia, and...

19:19.684 --> 19:22.852
...they really helped
put things into perspective.

19:22.854 --> 19:25.688
Who are these people?

19:25.690 --> 19:30.626
Leonard, friends are
like toilet paper.

19:30.628 --> 19:33.596
It's good to have extras
under the sink.

